'''沃尔巴克氏体属'''（[[學名|學名]]：{{lang|la|''Wolbachia''}}）為[[立克次体目|立克次体目]][[無形體科|無形體科]]的一[[属_(生物)|属]]，是一類感染[[节肢动物|节肢动物]]、包括很大部分[[昆虫|昆虫]]以及一些[[线虫|线虫]]的[[细菌|细菌]]。它是世界上最常见的[[寄生|寄生]][[微生物|微生物]]，可能是[[生物圈|生物圈]]最常见的寄生生物。沃尔巴克氏体感染能缩短[[果蝇|果蝇]]寿命。它与其宿主的交互过程很复杂，参与多种调控其寄主生殖活动的机制，有的涉及到[[互利共生|互利共生]]而非[[寄生|寄生]]。有的物种如果没有沃尔巴克氏体的寄生将不能生殖甚至不能生存。研究估计在[[新热带界|新热带界]]超过16%的昆虫感染了沃尔巴克氏体。<ref>{{Cite journal |last1=Werren |first1=J.H. |last2=Guo |first2=L |last3=Windsor |first3=D. W. |year=1995 |title=Distribution of ''Wolbachia'' among neotropical arthropods |journal=[[Proceedings_of_the_Royal_Society_B|Proceedings of the Royal Society B]] |volume=262 |issue=1364 |pages=197–204|bibcode=1995RSPSB.262..197W | doi=10.1098/rspb.1995.0196 }}</ref>全部昆虫物种的25-70%被估计是沃尔巴克氏体的潜在宿主。<ref>{{Cite journal |title=The Discovery of Wolbachia in Arthropods and Nematodes – A Historical Perspective |first1=Wieslaw J. |last1=Kozek |first2=Ramakrishna U. |last2=Rao |journal=Issues in Infectious Diseases |year=2007 |volume=5 |issue=''Wolbachia'': A Bug’s Life in another Bug |pages=1–14 |doi=10.1159/000104228 |series=Issues in Infectious Diseases |isbn=3-8055-8180-7}}</ref>沃尔巴克氏菌是自然界分布最为广泛的一种共生菌，在[[鞘翅目|鞘翅目]]、[[双翅目|双翅目]]、[[半翅目|半翅目]]、[[同翅目|同翅目]]、[[膜翅目|膜翅目]]、[[鳞翅目|鳞翅目]]、[[直翅目|直翅目]]和[[啮虫目|啮虫目]]等10多个目的150万一500万种昆虫中都有共生。

沃尔巴克氏体通过宿主的卵来垂直传播。沃尔巴克氏体演化出多种方式能最大限度地感染宿主所产的卵。

==历史==
1924年馬歇爾·赫爾廷（{{lang|en|Marshall Hertig}}）与{{le|西梅恩·伯特·沃爾巴克|Simeon Burt Wolbach}}在室内常见的[[尖音库蚊|尖音库蚊]]体内发现沃尔巴克氏体。1936年赫爾廷正式命名该物种为''{{lang|la|Wolbachia pipientis}}''。<ref>{{Cite journal |first1=Marshall |last1=Hertig |first2=S. Burt |last2=Wolbach |year=1924 |title=Studies on Rickettsia-Like Micro-Organisms in Insects |journal=Journal of Medical Research |volume=44 |pages=329–74 |pmc=2041761 |pmid=19972605 |issue=3}}</ref>1971年加州大学洛杉矶分校的Janice Yen与A. Ralph Barr发现被沃尔巴克氏体感染的雄性[[尖音库蚊|尖音库蚊]]的精子与未被沃尔巴克氏体感染的雌性[[尖音库蚊|尖音库蚊]]的卵子结合的受精卵由于[[细胞质不兼容|细胞质不兼容]]而死亡，<ref>{{Cite journal |author1=Yen JH |author2=Barr AR |year=1971 |title=New hypothesis of the cause of cytoplasmic incompatibility in ''Culex pipiens'' |journal=Nature |volume=232 |pages=657–8 |doi=10.1038/232657a0 |pmid=4937405 |issue=5313|bibcode = 1971Natur.232..657Y }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Insect Symbiosis |editor-first=Kostas |editor-last=Bourtzis |editor2-first=Thomas A. |editor2-last=Miller |isbn=9780849341946 |chapter=14: Insect pest control using Wolbachia and/or radiation |chapterurl=http://books.google.com/books?id=Y9_HAm28SoYC&pg=PA230 |page=230 |access-date=2015-06-12 |archive-date=2014-06-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140628073342/http://books.google.com/books?id=Y9_HAm28SoYC&pg=PA230 |dead-url=no }}</ref>科学界所后加强了对沃尔巴克氏体的研究。沃尔巴克氏体由于广泛分布、众多不同的演化交互、潜在地生物防控，具有巨大的研究价值。

==在宿主性别分化中的作用==
沃尔巴克氏体能够感染宿主的很多器官，但最重要的是感染[[睪丸|精巢]]与[[卵巢|卵巢]]。成熟的卵中有很多沃尔巴克氏体，但成熟的精子中没有沃尔巴克氏体。仅由被感染的雌性宿主把沃尔巴克氏体传播给后代。沃尔巴克氏体通过改变宿主的生殖能力极大化了其传播，有四种[[表型|表型]]：
* 雄性死亡：被感染的雄性在幼虫发育时死亡，这增加了被感染的雌性的出生率。<ref>{{cite journal | author = Hurst G. | year = 1999 | title = Male killing Wolbachia in two species of insects | url = | journal = [[Proceedings_of_the_Royal_Society_B|Proceedings of the Royal Society B]] | volume = 266 | issue = 1420| pages = 735–740 | author-separator = , | author2 = Jiggins F. M. | author3 = Graf von Der Schulenburg J. H. | author4 = Bertrand D. | display-authors = 4 | doi = 10.1098/rspb.1999.0698 | last5 = West | first5 = S. A. | last6 = Goriacheva | first6 = I. I. | last7 = Zakharov | first7 = I. A. | last8 = Werren | first8 = J. H. | last9 = Stouthamer | first9 = R. }}</ref>
* 雌性化：被感染的雄性发育为雌性或者不能生育的伪雌性。
* [[单性生殖|孤雌生殖]]：被感染的雌性的单性生殖。<ref>{{cite book |first1=Gerard J. |last1=Tortora |first2=Berdell R. |last2=Funke |first3=Cristine L. |last3=Case |title=Microbiology: an introduction |url=https://archive.org/details/microbiologyintr0009tort |publisher=Pearson Benjamin Cummings |year=2007 |isbn=0-8053-4790-9}}</ref>一个孤雌生殖的例子是[[赤眼蜂|赤眼蜂]]，<ref name="Knight2001">{{Cite journal |author=Knight J |date=5 July 2001 |title=Meet the Herod Bug |journal=Nature |volume=421 |pages=12–14 |doi=10.1038/35083744 |pmid=11452274 |issue=6842}}</ref>在感染沃尔巴克氏体情形下无需雄性也能生殖后代。在这个物种中，雄性非常罕见，可能已经被同一菌株的沃尔巴克氏体杀死。<ref>{{cite journal |title=Garden Friends & Foes: Trichogramma Wasps |url=http://whatcom.wsu.edu/ag/homehort/pest/trichogramma.htm |first=Todd |last=Murray |journal=Weeder's Digest |publisher=Washington State University Whatcom County Extension |accessdate=16 July 2009 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090621192656/http://whatcom.wsu.edu/ag/homehort/pest/trichogramma.htm |archivedate=2009年6月21日 }}<!-- possibly oclc=58592363 --></ref>
* [[细胞质不兼容|细胞质不兼容]]：被感染的雄性不能与未被感染的雌性繁殖，也不能与感染了其他[[基因型|基因型]]的雌性繁殖。

一些物种如果没有沃尔巴克氏体的寄生将不能生殖后代，有的甚至不能生存。<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Werren |first=John H. |date=February 2003 |title=Invasion of the Gender Benders: by manipulating sex and reproduction in their hosts, many parasites improve their own odds of survival and may shape the evolution of sex itself |journal=[[Natural_History_(magazine)|Natural History]] |volume=112 |issue=1 |page=58 |issn=0028-0712 |oclc=1759475 |url=http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m1134/is_1_112/ai_97174198 |format=Reprint |accessdate=15 November 2008 |archive-date=2012-07-08 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120708190307/http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m1134/is_1_112/ai_97174198/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

研究表明被感染的[[潮虫|潮虫]]具有极高比例的雌性比例。<ref>{{cite journal |first1=Thierry |last1=Rigaud |first2=Jérôme |last2=Moreau |first3=Pierre |last3=Juchault |date=October 1999 |title=Wolbachia infection in the terrestrial isopod Oniscus asellus: sex ratio distortion and effect on fecundity |journal=Heredity |volume=83 |issue=4 |pages=469–475 |pmid=10583549 |doi=10.1038/sj.hdy.6885990 |url=http://www.nature.com/hdy/journal/v83/n4/full/6885990a.html |access-date=2015-06-12 |archive-date=2016-03-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304051154/http://www.nature.com/hdy/journal/v83/n4/full/6885990a.html |dead-url=no }} However, the broods also often consisted of fewer eggs than the broods of the uninfected ''Oniscus asellus''.</ref>

沃尔巴克氏体在促进物种形成有重要作用。<ref>{{Cite journal |first1=Seth R. |last1=Bordenstein |first2=O'Hara |last2=Patrick |first3=John H. |last3=Werren |title=Wolbachia-induced incompatibility precedes other hybrid incompatibilities in Nasonia |journal=[[Nature_(journal)|Nature]] |volume=409 |issue=6821 |pages=675–7 |doi=10.1038/35055543 |pmid=11217858 |bibcode=2001Natur.409..707B |year=2001}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |last=Zimmer |first=Carl |authorlink=Carl Zimmer |year=2001 |title=Wolbachia: A Tale of Sex and Survival |journal=[[Science_(journal)|Science]] |volume=292 |issue=5519 |pages=1093–5 |doi=10.1126/science.292.5519.1093 |url=http://carlzimmer.com/articles/2001.php?subaction=showfull&id=1177558753&archive=&start_from=&ucat=4& |pmid=11352061 |author= |access-date=2015-06-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071007095923/http://carlzimmer.com/articles/2001.php?subaction=showfull&id=1177558753&archive=&start_from=&ucat=4& |archive-date=2007-10-07 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |first1=Arndt |last1=Telschow |first2=Matthias |last2=Flor |first3=Yutaka |last3=Kobayashi |first4=Peter |last4=Hammerstein |first5=John H. |last5=Werren |year=2007 |title=Wolbachia-Induced Unidirectional Cytoplasmic Incompatibility and Speciation: Mainland-Island Model |journal=[[Plos_One|Plos One]] |volume=2 |issue=1 |pages=e701 |doi=10.1371/journal.pone.0000701 |pmid=17684548 |pmc=1934337 |editor1-last=Rees |editor1-first=Mark|bibcode = 2007PLoSO...2..701T }}</ref>沃尔巴克氏体菌株打乱了宿主的性别比这改变了自然宿主的性选择模式。<ref>{{cite journal | author = Charlat S. | year = 2006 | title = Male-killing bacteria trigger a cycle of increasing male fatigue and female promiscuity | url = | journal = Current Biology | volume = 17 | issue = 3| pages = 273–7 | author-separator = , | author2 = Reuter M. | author3 = Dyson E.A. | author4 = Hornett E.A. | author5 = Duplouy A.M.R. | author6 = Davies N. | author7 = Roderick G. | author8 = Wedell N. | author9 = Hurst G.D.D.  | pmid = 17276921 | doi = 10.1016/j.cub.2006.11.068 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | author = JIGGINS F. M. | year = 2000 | title = Sex ratio distorting Wolbachia cause sex role reversal in their butterfly hosts | url = | journal = [[Proceedings_of_the_Royal_Society_B|Proceedings of the Royal Society B]] | volume = 267 | issue = 1438| pages = 69–73 | doi = 10.1098/rspb.2000.0968 | last2 = Hurst | first2 = G. D. D. | last3 = Majerus | first3 = M. E. N. }}</ref>并且产生了非常强的选择压力，导致一些极快的在自然群体中自然选择的例子。<ref>{{cite journal | doi = 10.1126/science.1143369 | title = Extraordinary Flux in Sex Ratio | year = 2007 | last1 = Charlat | first1 = S. | last2 = Hornett | first2 = E. A. | last3 = Fullard | first3 = J. H. | last4 = Davies | first4 = N. | last5 = Roderick | first5 = G. K. | last6 = Wedell | first6 = N. | last7 = Hurst | first7 = G. D. D. | journal = Science | volume = 317 | issue = 5835 | pages = 214 | pmid = 17626876 |bibcode = 2007Sci...317..214C }}</ref>

